Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language modeling using recurrent neural networks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses various compression techniques for neural networks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the efficiency of neural networks for real-time applications.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper specifically focuses on compression techniques for recurrent neural networks.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with image or video data, but some of the compression techniques discussed may be applicable to computer vision models.
